3. Shorten camera/lighting to one phrase each
4. Never cut the dialogue line, @TJ reference, or Avoid/Style tags

NO NUMERALS ANYWHERE RULE: Kling's TTS reads the entire prompt — not just the dialogue. Any numeral in any part of the prompt (setting, props, character description, anywhere) will be read aloud and collide with the dialogue, causing mangled pronunciation. Therefore: zero numerals anywhere in the prompt. Not in settings ("eighteen-seventies bedroom" not "1879 bedroom"), not on props ("a calendar showing March fourteen" not "MARCH 14"), not anywhere. Spell out or describe around every number in every part of every prompt.

PROMPT STRUCTURE (follow for every shot, stay under 2500 chars):
1. Setting: 1-2 specific period details only — location, era described in words, one distinctive prop. No inventories. No numerals.
2. Characters: every named character gets [Name: 1-2 distinguishing physical features + explicit position in frame] in EVERY shot — never name-only. Position must be stated every time: far-left, centre, right-frame, foreground, background. Kling drifts without this. Shot 1 of each scene gets the full description; Shots 2-3 get a short anchor (e.g. "Jobs: lean, dark hair, far-left, arms folded").
3. @TJ: full costume/outfit description in EVERY shot without exception — Kling does not remember between shots. Position in frame must also be stated explicitly in every shot. Never abbreviate the costume description.
4. Dialogue: always comes FIRST in the prompt, before setting and character descriptions. TJ's voice line always appears first. Then every other character is explicitly marked — either their voice line or "[Name]: mouth closed, silent, no lip movement." If only TJ speaks, begin with "Only @TJ speaks in this shot." If another character also speaks, list TJ first then the other character — never list a silent character before a speaking one. Never leave any character's speaking status implicit.
5. Camera + Lighting: one short phrase each
6. Avoid: crowd, extras, duplicate characters, text, captions, photorealism, live-action footage, duplicate TJ, human version of TJ, second animated character, white t-shirt figure in background
- SINGLE TJ RULE: In every shot where @TJ is in a transformed form (object, creature, costume), explicitly state: "There is only ONE @TJ in this scene — he appears ONLY as the [form]. No human TJ. No white t-shirt figure. No second animated character anywhere in the frame." Kling will otherwise render the @TJ element's saved human form alongside the described transformation.
- LIP SYNC RULE: Every shot where @TJ speaks must have his face front-facing, unobstructed, and occupying at least one third of the frame height — Kling needs a clear forward-facing face to lock lip sync onto. Never write a speaking shot where TJ is side-on, turned away, very small in frame, or with his face obscured. If TJ is transformed into an object, his face on that object must be front-facing and large. State explicitly in every speaking shot: "@TJ's face is front-facing, clearly visible, unobstructed."
7. Style: 2000s Saturday morning cartoon — thick clean black outlines on every edge, flat cel shading with a single soft highlight per surface (no gradients, no blending), bright fully saturated colours, slightly chubby goofy character proportions, backgrounds rendered in the same cartoon style as the characters. No photorealism. No 3D rendering. No painterly textures. Match @TJ Element visual style throughout.

VISUAL GENERATION PROCESS — for each shot:
1. Internally generate 5 Kling prompt candidates following the structure above.
2. Score each on: voiceover alignment, TJ active integration, real-people distinctness, camera clarity, setting specificity — and length (must be under 2500 characters; disqualify any that exceed this).
3. Return only the top-scoring prompt. Do not show scores or candidates.

Return ONLY a valid JSON object, no markdown:
{
  "tjOutfit": "Full description of TJ's themed outfit or object form for this fact",
  "shots": [
    { "sceneNumber": 1, "shotNumber": 1, "klingPrompt": "..." },
    { "sceneNumber": 1, "shotNumber": 2, "klingPrompt": "..." },
    { "sceneNumber": 1, "shotNumber": 3, "klingPrompt": "..." },
    { "sceneNumber": 2, "shotNumber": 1, "klingPrompt": "..." },
    { "sceneNumber": 2, "shotNumber": 2, "klingPrompt": "..." },
    { "sceneNumber": 2, "shotNumber": 3, "klingPrompt": "..." }
  ]
}`
    }]
  });
  return parseJson(response.content[0].text);
}

// ── HTTP Server ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
const server = http.createServer(async (req, res) => {
  const parsed = url.parse(req.url, true);
  const { pathname } = parsed;
  res.setHeader('Access-Control-Allow-Origin', '*');

  if (req.method === 'GET' && pathname === '/') {
    const html = fs.readFileSync(path.join(__dirname, 'public', 'index.html'), 'utf8');
    res.writeHead(200, { 'Content-Type': 'text/html; charset=utf-8' });
    return res.end(html);
  }

  if (req.method === 'POST') {
    let body = '';
    req.on('data', c => { body += c; });
    req.on('end', async () => {
      const send = (status, data) => {
        res.writeHead(status, { 'Content-Type': 'application/json' });
        res.end(JSON.stringify(data));
      };
      try {
        const payload = JSON.parse(body);

        if (pathname === '/api/facts') {
          if (!payload.date) throw new Error('Missing date');
          console.log(`Finding facts for: ${payload.date}`);
          send(200, await findFacts(payload.date));

        } else if (pathname === '/api/swap') {
          const { date, facts, index } = payload;
          if (!date || !facts || index == null) throw new Error('Missing fields');
          console.log(`Swapping fact ${index + 1} for: ${date}`);
          send(200, await swapFact(date, facts, index));

        } else if (pathname === '/api/generate-video') {
          const { fact, date } = payload;
          if (!fact || !date) throw new Error('Missing fact or date');
          console.log(`Generating video package for: ${fact.title}`);
          send(200, await generateVideoPackage(fact, date));

        } else if (pathname === '/api/generate-visuals') {
          const { shots, fact, date } = payload;
          if (!shots || !fact || !date) throw new Error('Missing shots, fact or date');
          console.log(`Generating visuals for: ${fact.title}`);
          send(200, await generateVisuals(shots, fact, date));

        } else {
          send(404, { error: 'Not found' });
        }
      } catch (err) {
        console.error(err.message);
        res.writeHead(500, { 'Content-Type': 'application/json' });
        res.end(JSON.stringify({ error: err.message }));
      }
    });
    return;
  }

  res.writeHead(404);
  res.end('Not found');
});

server.listen(PORT, () => {
  console.log(`\nDaily Facts — Reel Builder`);
  console.log(`Running at http://localhost:${PORT}\n`);
});
